          <placeName xml:id="name499-4" xml:lang="ar">معرة النعمان</placeName>
          <placeName xml:id="name499-5" xml:lang="ar" source="#bib499-1">المعرة</placeName>
          <placeName xml:id="name499-6" xml:lang="ar" source="#bib499-1">معرة النعمان</placeName>
          <desc type="abstract" xml:id="abstract499-1" xml:lang="en">“Maʿarrat al-Nuʿmān, famous as the birthplace of the blind poet al-Maʿarrī [q.v.], is situated at about 500 m. altitude, in lat. 35° 38′ N. and long. 36° 40′ E. Falling within northern Phoenicia, two days’ journey to the south of Ḥalab or Aleppo (70 km.), it is situated on the eastern fringe of a massif rich in archaeological remains.” (Elisséeff)</desc>
